Amazing service, fantastic food, lovely atmosphere. The back patio is a charming setup with enough greenery to make you forget you're in Brooklyn, livening up your lunch or dinner tenfold. The vast wine selection should cater to just about any taste, and the rotating menu provides a guarantee of a fresh and well prepared meal with every visit. The only thing keeping me from going to Bacchus every day is the price, which is reasonable considering the quality of food and service, but a bit high for my budget. Overall, a fantastic establishment, and the epitome of Brooklyn dining.

We can’t say enough about how amazing the venue and especially the staff are at Bacchus Bistro. We had our wedding ceremony and reception at Bacchus in June 2019 and everything was perfect. Meryl and Alvaro are a dream team that took care of every single detail from the moment we decided to have our wedding at Bacchus up until the day after the wedding when we picked up our leftover decorations.  Bacchus is an amazing venue at a great value and exactly what we wanted for our wedding – an intimate (55 people) and personal backyard garden ceremony, a dinner-focused celebration with high quality food, and a perfect space to dance the night away.  The food is beyond delicious and beautifully presented. The garden space is flawlessly set up for a cozy and intimate ceremony and reception. We were also able to reserve a room inside the restaurant attached to the outdoor gardens for dancing which made everything flow seamlessly.  As an added bonus Meryl went above and beyond in helping us coordinate the event. Meryl is extremely detail oriented and walked us through every step of the process. Along with Alvaro and the rest of the wonderful staff at Bacchus, they helped us plan and pull off a beautiful celebration. The staff are the best of the best and made our wedding unforgettable. I can’t thank them enough for giving us a perfect wedding day.

"Impressed" is a word I usually reserve for when I have low expectations that are moderately exceeded, and I say it in a slightly high pitched tone that my cousin Brian calls "pretentious". This is not one of those occasions. I was sincerely impressed by Bacchus.  Our appetizers and entrees were amazing, hands down the best octopus and best gnocchi I've had in recent memory (possibly ever). Everything was pretty classically French, but with a modern spin that kept it interesting. The desserts didn't have the modern spin, but were perfectly executed classics.  I don't think I've ever had a meal this good for this low a price, and considering the normal markup on Brooklyn, that's saying something. Appetizers, entrees, desserts, and a bottle of wine came out to about $50 per person, but if you only ordered entrees you could keep it in the $20-30 range very easily

The hanger steak appetizer was perfectly cooked - that peanut butter sauce unlike any other. The snails cooked in the she'll with delicious garlic butter. Duck rillet was just perfect - a nice pate-like consistency. For the mains I had the duck magret and it was just right. Medium/Medium rare and tasty enough that I finished the entire thing. Baked potatoes and mushrooms and all . If it's a nice warm evening, enjoy their lovely outside seating area.

Phenomenal French cuisine. They also have a bottomless mimosa/Bellini brunch deal on the weekend that will rock your socks. The croque madame, the croque monsieur, and the quiche lorraine are top notch. The red wine lamb shank might have changed my life. They have also have a great wine selection.

Twas the night before Christmas and Bacchus was short-staffed and did not have enough mussels. I knew something was off when the waitress said they ran out of sparkling water and could only serve us tap water. As an appetizer we had the tuna avacodo tartare which was ok. There was more avacado than tuna and the appetizer came with only two crustinis, which was not enough for this type of dish. I ordered the seafood pappardele which arrived lukewarm and portions of the mussels were cold. The mussels were very fishy tasting and I could not finish eating them. There was one clam and one scallop in the dish. The shrimp was fine; the calamari ok. The sauce was watered down. Overall the dish was not good for the price charged. My date tried to order the mussels and fries dish and was told no by the waitress. She said they were saving mussels for the pappardele dishes and did not have enough. How does a French restaurant not have enough mussels for Christmas Eve dinner at 7pm?! My date settled for a burger with fries which was underwhelming. No ketchup was offered with the fries until my date finally flagged a food runner who finally brought it after the fries were already cold. The waitress was nowhere to be found and did not check in with us as to whether the food was OK. Other guests were also looking around for service and appeared annoyed that the restaurant did not have enough mussels on Christmas Eve. This was a very poor Christmas Eve experience and we could not wait to leave the restaurant. We did not even bother asking for the dessert menu. I had high hopes as the reviews seemed good for this place but unfortunately we would not recommend going here. And we don't plan to return.

We LOVE Bacchus! If we could give them more stars we would! We found Bacchus a little over a year ago when we were looking for a wedding venue. We looked at a lot of places but when we walked in I knew this was the one. We got married there September 2018.  After deciding on Bacchus for our wedding we went there a lot over the next year—dinner, drinks, meeting our wedding vendors. The staff was always so lovely, warm, and accommodating. The food always so yummy.  Meryl is the best! She, Alvaro, and team are really on top of their game. You get early on that they are there to make your wedding day the wedding day you imagined.  They are professional, flexible, and warm. We really felt they cared about us and what they were doing.  The space is beautiful. The tree in the garden with twinkle lights—stunning! The food—let’s just say Yum!  Our guests raved about the space, the service, and the food. The trifecta!  Meryl, thank you for helping to make our day perfect---because it was! Excellent meal, good service, professional and pleasant wait staff.

THE GOOD: The Bacchus salad and citrus salad are amazing. The chicken dish with julienne veggies and mash was the best! The chocolate hazelnut cake was so good. THE OKAY: The chocolate mousse was good but I wasn't blown away. The flavor of the crab cake is good but it doesn't taste like crab. THE BAD: The wines taste no different than box wine. The duck was like chewing a salty rubber band(no exaggeration). The salmon burger should be taken off the menu, it doesn't even taste like salmon, it looks like that weird green padding under carpet, not edible. The steak had no seasoning on it, not even salt and it was chewy. LOCATION: its downtown Brooklyn which means no street parking. AMBIANCE: Intimate, cozy and nice music. BATHROOM: Clean Overall I would definitely return because that chicken dish and salads are tony the tiger greaaat!
